# No fatal checks on client-controlled state

Request-reachable code must **return `absl::Status`** (mapped to gRPC/HTTP errors
by the gateway), not abort the engine via `CHECK`, `LOG(FATAL)`,
`InsertOrDie`, or `InsertIfNotPresent`-as-die.

## Applies to

- Query handlers (`QueryService::DryRun`, `Query`, DDL paths)
- Catalog construction and registration (`GoogleSqlCatalog`, view/UDF/TVF/
  procedure registries, replay into `SimpleCatalog`)
- Any path a client can drive through SQL, REST, or gRPC

## Allowed fatals

- Programmer errors on **internal** invariants (null deps injected by our own
  code, impossible enum values after our own switches)
- Startup / one-time init that cannot run without fixed configuration

When leaving a fatal, add a one-line comment explaining why the condition is
**unreachable from clients**.

## Patterns

| Avoid | Prefer |
|-------|--------|
| `InsertOrDie(&map, key, val)` on names from SQL/REST | Check insert; return `AlreadyExists` / `InvalidArgument` |
| `CHECK(insert_ok)` on catalog replay | Dedup by name; skip or replace; lazy resolve (see `FindProjectView`) |
| Destroying registry objects while catalogs hold raw pointers | Retire into a side vector; purge from catalog on replay |

